{"履修期": "秋学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">This course builds on the communication skills that were covered in the spring semester. Students will improve their speaking and listening ability through a variety of activities, including listening and note-taking, making recordings, shadowing, and giving presentations. These are the goals: </span></span><br /><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">• To equip students with English speaking and listening skills </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">• To provide students with guidance and practice in basic conversation </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">• To develop students' academic listening, speaking and presentation skills </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">• To help students improve their English comprehensibility through pronunciation practice </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">• To improve TOEIC scores</span></span>", "到達目標": "<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">In the fall semester we will continue to use the same learning goals as in the spring. </span></span><br /><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">1. Group Discussion Skills </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">a. Expressing ideas, asking for information or clarification </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">b. Giving reasons, evaluating ideas </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">c. Agreeing and disagreeing </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">d. Communication strategies </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">e Negotiation strategies </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">f. Debate strategies </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">2. Presentation/Speaking Skills </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">a. Speech preparation and practice </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">b. Speech delivery </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">c. Speaking fluency, pronunciation, and intonation\t </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">3. TOEIC Skills </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">a. TOEIC listening skills </span></span><br /><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">b. Grammar and Vocabulary</span></span>", "特記事項": "本授業科目は、“オンライン授業60単位制限対象科目”ではありません。 The course is not subject to the 60-credit limit for online courses.<br />【合併】英語コミュニケーションIIＢ　５（理学部）/英語コミュニケーションIIＢ　５（理工学部）/英語コミュニケーションIIＢ　５（工学部）/英語コミュニケーションIIＢ　５（生命環境学部）", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">This course has face-to-face classes and an online component. If conditions permit we will have face-to-face classes, with content delivered online. If we are unable to have face-to-face classes we will have both on- demand online classes with optional live Zoom classes.</span></span>", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-alig